{
  "texts": [
    "1) Embodied self-care.",
    "Embodiment is already a topic of current research in AI (see, for example, Duan et al. 2022), but its link with AI ethics is less thoroughly explored.",
    "Embodiment would situate the subject in space and time, providing the facticity needed to contextualise its speech and actions.",
    "Crucially, embodiment serves as a \"face\", a concrete \"living presence\" that disrupts and confounds the reduction of the Other to mere object (Levinas 2012).",
    "This would enact a bidirectional relation between AI and human beings."
  ]
}